# Cloudflare Workers

Workers are edge compute functions that run JavaScript/TypeScript/Wasm in V8 isolates. They handle HTTP requests, run cron schedules, and process queue messages.

## Quick Start

```bash
# Create a new Worker project
npm create cloudflare@latest my-worker

# Or manually:
mkdir my-worker && cd my-worker
npm init -y
npm install wrangler --save-dev
```

## wrangler.toml

```toml
name = "my-worker"
main = "src/index.ts"
compatibility_date = "2024-09-23"
compatibility_flags = ["nodejs_compat"]
account_id = "your-account-id"

# Optional: custom domain or route
# routes = [{ pattern = "api.example.com/*", zone_name = "example.com" }]
```

## Worker Entry Point (Module Syntax)

```typescript
// src/index.ts
export interface Env {
  MY_KV: KVNamespace;       // KV binding
  MY_BUCKET: R2Bucket;      // R2 binding
  MY_DB: D1Database;        // D1 binding
  API_KEY: string;          // Environment variable
}

export default {
  async fetch(request: Request, env: Env, ctx: ExecutionContext): Promise<Response> {
    const url = new URL(request.url);

    if (url.pathname === '/api/hello') {
      return Response.json({ message: 'Hello from the edge!' });
    }

    if (url.pathname === '/api/data') {
      const value = await env.MY_KV.get('key');
      return Response.json({ value });
    }

    return new Response('Not Found', { status: 404 });
  },

  // Cron trigger (configured in wrangler.toml)
  async scheduled(event: ScheduledEvent, env: Env, ctx: ExecutionContext) {
    ctx.waitUntil(doScheduledWork(env));
  },
};
```

## Deployment

```bash
# Deploy to production
wrangler deploy

# Deploy to a specific environment
wrangler deploy --env staging

# Local development
wrangler dev

# Local dev with remote bindings (real KV, R2, D1)
wrangler dev --remote

# View live logs
wrangler tail
```

## Request/Response Patterns

```typescript
// Read request body
const body = await request.json();
const formData = await request.formData();
const text = await request.text();

// Headers
const auth = request.headers.get('Authorization');
const cf = request.cf; // Cloudflare-specific: country, colo, tlsVersion

// Responses
return new Response('OK', { status: 200 });
return Response.json({ data: 'value' });
return Response.redirect('https://example.com', 301);
return new Response(readableStream, {
  headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/octet-stream' },
});
```

## Environment Variables and Secrets

```toml
# wrangler.toml — plain text vars
[vars]
API_URL = "https://api.example.com"
ENVIRONMENT = "production"
```

```bash
# Secrets (encrypted, not in wrangler.toml)
wrangler secret put API_KEY
# Enter value when prompted

# List secrets
wrangler secret list

# Delete a secret
wrangler secret delete API_KEY
```

## Cron Triggers

```toml
# wrangler.toml
[triggers]
crons = ["0 * * * *", "*/5 * * * *"]
```

```typescript
export default {
  async scheduled(event, env, ctx) {
    // event.cron contains the cron pattern that triggered this
    // event.scheduledTime is the trigger timestamp
    ctx.waitUntil(processData(env));
  },
};
```

## Sub-Skills

- **[[cloudflare/workers/routes]]** — Configure routes, custom domains, and zone bindings
- **[[cloudflare/workers/bindings]]** — Connect Workers to KV, R2, D1, Queues, and other services

## Runtime Constraints

- Uses Web Standards APIs, not Node.js. Enable `nodejs_compat` flag for Node.js API polyfills
- 128MB memory limit per invocation
- Free: 10ms CPU time, 1MB script. Paid: 30s CPU time, 10MB script
- `request.cf` object provides geo data: `country`, `city`, `timezone`, `colo`
- `ctx.waitUntil(promise)` for background work after response is sent
- `ctx.passThroughOnException()` falls back to origin on uncaught errors
